{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7cc48dde-5e3b-4c3d-8438-127616a3280a","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing a .NET crash dump. Here are the main approaches:\n\n### 1. **`dotnet-dump` (recommended, cross-platform)**\n```bash\n# Install\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Analyze\ndotnet-dump analyze <your-file.dmp>\n\n# Useful commands inside the analyzer:\n#   clrstack          - managed call stacks\n#   pe                - print last exception\n#   dumpheap -stat    - heap summary\n#   threads           - list all threads\n#   setthread <id>    - switch thread\n#   clrstack -all     - all thread stacks\n```\n\n### 2. **`lldb` with SOS (Linux)**\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core <your-file.dmp>\n# Then: clrstack, pe, dso, etc.\n```\n\n### 3. **WinDbg / Visual Studio (Windows)**\nOpen the `.dmp` in Visual Studio or WinDbg with the SOS extension.\n\n---\n\n### Quick triage steps:\n1. **`pe`** — print the exception that caused the crash\n2. **`threads`** → find the faulting thread\n3. **`clrstack`** — get the managed stack trace\n4. **`dso`** — dump stack objects for context\n\nWould you like me to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your file? If so, tell me the path to the `.dmp` file and I'll walk through it interactively.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"de3973bc-21c9-4be4-948a-593ee7cb2c12","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking for help analyzing a .NET crash dump (.dmp file). This is a general troubleshooting/debugging question rather than something tied to the repository. Let me provide guidance on how to analyze a .dmp file from a .NET application.\n\nI don't see a .dmp file in the working directory, and the user says they \"already have\" one but hasn't specified where it is. Let me give them practical guidance on how to analyze it.\n\nLet me check what tools are available in the environment that could help with this.","outputTokens":495,"requestId":"C3C3:86E8:1D1F08D:20C21D5:6A07C3AD"},"id":"7bbaf43f-20